message.content:
To get to the grocery store that is 1km away in Swaziland, you have a few options:

1. Walking: If the weather is pleasant and you enjoy walking, you can simply walk to the grocery store. It will take approximately 10-15 minutes to cover a distance of 1km on foot.

2. Cycling: If you have a bicycle or can rent one, cycling can be a convenient and faster option. It will take around 3-5 minutes to reach the store by bike.

3. Public Transportation: Check if there are any local buses or minibusses that pass by or near the grocery store. You can inquire about the nearest bus stop and take a bus to reach your destination.

4. Taxi: Taxis are readily available in Swaziland, and you can easily find one to take you to the grocery store. It might be a bit more expensive than other options, but it offers convenience and saves time.

Consider choosing the mode of transportation that suits your preferences, budget, and the local conditions.
